And the three vast loaves of the world 's best -LRB- and probably most expensive -RRB- sourdough bread from the Meyers Bageri on Kongensgade -LRB- owned by Claus Meyer of Noma -RRB- which we rammed into our hand luggage and have been eating ever since .

The Danes are big on cosiness -- or Hygge , as they call it . They 're the masters of attractive ambience -- candles , wonderful lighting , pleasing lines and smooth wood , even in McDonald 's . Given time was short over a weekend , we spent it mostly being ` cosy ' .

From the launchpad of our incredibly central hotel , we concentrated our efforts in an array of cafes , wine bars -LRB- particularly the brilliant Ved Stranden 10 , near Christiansborg Palace -RRB- , restaurants and , thanks to visiting in the middle of the ` Wondercool Copenhagen jazz and art festival ' , experienced Danish ` supergroup ' , the Mountains -LRB- surprisingly good -RRB- and the truly wonderful Danish pianist Carsten Dahl .

